what follow-up statenents given: Thank you! The reason I answered that I feel the subject is because in all the subjects we do, it doesn’t necessarily mean that we understand them all. So when a teacher is teaching, you start to select the subjects you are good at. Like if it’s mathematics you say, I understand it and if it’s chemistry you say, I understand it. So when you are about to do it and you know you understand the subject you are about to do, it makes you feel happy to do it and feel confident in yourself as well.

what follow-up statenents given:
Translation: Maybe an example, I might come to study and the teacher goes out without me understanding anything in all the things he taught, because it may depend on a person but if I come in saying “I understand chemistry” I feel like I didn’t come to study for nothing or for no reason and that I go home with something. 
Dominik: And chemistry for example, what is it that you take home?
Student: Like if the teacher teaches us the way reactions are mixed and gives a certain solution, when I get home and they ask me what I has learned; I tell them about how when reactions are mixed it gives out other solutions.

statement_Kinyarwanda: AMASOMO AMWE NA AMWE ABA ADUKOMEREYE TUTAYIYUMVA MO BITYO NTITUYAHE AGACIRO BAMWE NA BAMWE ABANDI TUKIHATIRA KUYASOBANUKIRWA

name: Dukuzimana Fabrice

statement_English: SOME SUBJECTS ARE HARD/DIFFICULT FOR US AND WE DON'T LIKE THEM, SO SOME OF US DON'T GIVE THEM MUCH IMPORTANCE WHILE I AND OTHERS FORCE OURSELVES TO UNDERSTAND THEM

Translation: I will explain, the reason why I said that it will make my parent, and my family happy, is because when I succeed/pass and show it to them, they too see that I have confidence, they are so happy/pleased because they can see that I am confident.
Dominik: Would you say, students that are not confident, they don’t think they make their family proud?
Student: yego, kubera ko abatifitiye ikizere ntabyo yashimisha n’umuryango we, Ibyo akora ntabyo babyemera nta n’ubwo babyishimira.
Translation: Yes, because they are not confident, they can’t make their family happy. The family doesn’t agree with what they are doing and they are not happy/pleased with it.

statement_Kinyarwanda: NI KUBERA KO MURUGO HABA HARI IMIRIMO MYINSHI
statement_English: IT IS BECAUSE, AT HOME THERE'S A LOT OF WORK

name: Niyomurinzi Pacifique
what follow-up statenents given:
(AN): It is like when you are going back home and you see other kids are playing football, and you see how much the game is fun and you feel the urge to play and go to play. Then when you start playing, you get home late at night and start to work on domestic works, and do not get enough time to revise his lessons.
(DN): But why is this demotivating if you don’t have enough time to revise?
(PQ):  There is a time that you study without confidence, and would say many people studied and they are sitting with their diplomas. And would ask myself why I am studying if those who finished do not have jobs. And say let me study just to make a point and think that maybe I will have a chance and succeed. But you don’t have confidence, that is the reason.   
(DN): Do you want to say because quiet often you don’t revise or you don’t have time to revise, you just feel you cannot do it anyway?
(PQ): Yes.

what follow-up statenents given: (AN): There are things that I know a lot, maybe when a parent says “if you don’t go to school, you won’t achieve anything” and I wonder why does he/she loves me while he/she didn’t study?” For example, my mom, she did not study but I wonder, there are time a parent mistreats his/her child. The parent makes tough studying and tell his/her child that if he/she doesn’t go to school, he/she won’t achieve anything and he/she won’t become a better person.  Then that is where you find a child with a lot of problems. Then whenever, I think that there are other bunch of peoples who are done with their studies and are jobless. Then that makes me to think that if you study or not, all it is a gift from God. What you will become doesn’t go anywhere.

name: Umufasha Somaya
what follow-up statenents given: What I wanted to say, a person can do a given thing without confidence and makes him fail. But there are times that a person does something and feels confident because he/she will succeed in what he/she is doing.
statement_Kinyarwanda: IBYO NKORA BYOSE NSHOBORA KUBIKORA KUBERA KO IBISUZO MBA NATANZE MBA BYIZEYE
statement_English: THAT WHATEVER I'M DOING IS RIGHT BECAUSE I AM CONFIDENT WITH THE ANSWERS I GIVE

name: Umufasha Somaya
what follow-up statenents given:
(AN): There is a time that a person does something but doesn’t want to do it and he/she fails it. but whenever you do something feeling well in your body, it makes you feel that you can succeed. Like you can do a revision while you are at home and without confidence, you can succeed.
(DN): And then why would you do it gladly?
(SM): You can do something without loving it and makes you not to do it well. Then to make me succeed, if I am not confident, it can’t help me to focus and work well. when I am confident, I work well
statement_Kinyarwanda: MBA NUMVA KO IBYO NKORA BYOSE ARIBYO KANDI NKABIKORA MBIKUNZE
statement_English: I FEEL LIKE WHATEVER I AM DOING IS RIGHT AND I DO IT GLADLY
statement_stem: MBA NUMVA KO IBYO NKORA BYOSE ARIBYO

name: Umufasha Somaya
what follow-up statenents given:
(AN): There is a time that a person does something but doesn’t want to do it and he/she fails it. but whenever you do something feeling well in your body, it makes you feel that you can succeed. Like you can do a revision while you are at home and without confidence, you can succeed.
(DN): And then why would you do it gladly?
(SM): You can do something without loving it and makes you not to do it well. Then to make me succeed, if I am not confident, it can’t help me to focus and work well. when I am confident, I work well
statement_Kinyarwanda: MBA NUMVA KO IBYO NKORA BYOSE ARIBYO KANDI NKABIKORA MBIKUNZE
statement_English: I FEEL THAT EVERYTHING I DO IS CORRECT AND THEN I DO IT WITH LOVE

name: Umufasha Somaya
what follow-up statenents given:
(AN): When you have confidence in you, you have to think well. So, would I think well if I am not confident? It can happen. But when you are confident, it makes you think critically. For instance, if you have subjects that you did not understand well in class, you can seek for help or also find a way to explain them to yourself, or you can go and seek help at home.
(DN): But then what does it have to do with to think well?
(SM): If other students explain to you and you are not focusing, you can’t understand it because you are not thinking. For instance, no one can explain to me while I am making noise and say I will understand. But when you think and pay attention to what your fellow is telling you, you can comprehend what you wanted to know

what follow-up statenents given:
(JN): I wanted to say that to be confident it is good because when you are not confident, you can’t do anything and accomplish it. To be confident is good to someone who has a goal because you can’t be depressed.
(DN): But if you say it feels it is good. What do you think it is good when you have confidence?
(JN): It makes you not being depressed, worried, makes you energize, and makes you feel strong, and makes you to not losing hope. It makes you feel you are able. When someone is confident, he/she feels how it is good and makes him/her think about a lot of things.
(DN): Would you say being confident feels good?  Is it what you meant or something else?
(JN): I wanted to say that once you are confident, you feel good because you believe in yourself and feel that what you want to accomplish will be accomplished.

name: Umuraza Jeannette
what follow-up statenents given:
(JN): When you do understand a subject, you can even answer to it.  Because when they bring questions, you fail at those questions and lose hope and motivation of studying that subject.
(DN): If you say a subject is difficult, do you basically mean you don’t understand the subject?
(JN): No, there is a time that the subject might be difficult but you want to understand it. However, you focus on that subject depends on how you want to study it.
(DN): What do you mean if you say a subject is difficult?
(JN): For instance, to answer questions in chemistry is difficult. It is also a challenge for teachers because they do not have enough materials for practice and becomes an obstacle for your learning. Then, once, we are in the national examination, they bring various questions. Same as we did for district exams, most of the questions asked were not seen in class.
(DN): Actually, we once asked two students what does it mean if a subject is difficult? One student said if a subject is difficult you just don’t understand it.  Another student said if a subject is difficult you can still understand it, you just need to put in more work. Who of the two students is right, what do you think?
(JN): The second student was right because you just need to put in more work and understand the subject.
(DN): Why do you think the second one is right?
(JN): It is because when you don’t understand a subject, you can’t come to its end and if they bring a quiz and say you don’t understand it and score a zero, no. You try your best so that you can’t score a zero, and try to succeed.

statement_English: WHEN WE ARE GIVEN AN EXERCISE ON A LESSON WE JUST STUDIED AND WE ARE DIVIDED INTO GROUPS, YOU MIGHT NOT UNDERSTAND IT WHEN THE TEACHER IS TEACHING IT BUT WITH THE GROUP, THERE IS A WAY THEY GET TO EXPLAIN IT TO YOU AND YOU GET TO UNDERSTAND IT BETTER THAN WHEN THE TEACHER WAS THE ONE TEACHING. AND YOU ARE ABLE TO DO IT ON YOUR OWN

statement_English: AT TIMES YOU WANT TO GO THROUGH THE IT AGAIN, SO THAT IF YOU DID NOT UNDERSTAND IT YOU MIGHT ASK YOUR FRIEND, AND THEY EXPLAIN A CERTAIN QUESTION TO YOU SO THAT WHEN YOU ARE GIVEN THOSE EXERCISES YOUR ABLE TO UNDERSTAND IT BETTER

statement_English: WHEN IT'S ALMOST TIME FOR THE EXAM AND THERE ARE SOME OF WHAT YOU HAVE LEARNED EARLIER  THAT YOU MAY NOT STILL REMEMBER, YOU TAKE THE OPPORTUNITY TO ASK FOR HELP SO THAT YOU REMEMBER IT WHEN IT IS SET IN THE EXAM
